|CKBSucker Punch: Fairness Was Never in the Contract|000

Syntax: suckerpunch [foe]
Alias:  spunch

Every Rank 1 Charlatan can exploit a melee opening with a current weapon or
their own regrettably effective hands. A foe already paralyzed or unable to
concentrate leaves room for a much harder blow, making confuse and distract
excellent opening arguments. When that opening is there, Sucker Punch says so
explicitly. Misdirection adds force to the trick.

At Misdirection 4, a second wielded weapon joins the pitch. This is a
close-range trick; no amount of confidence lets your fist cross a room.
